tories, so resume and revisit are the default behaviors rather than an afterthought.\ndocs/product-brief.md:24:4. Story pitches generated by Gemini, with selection, refinement, or regeneration.\ndocs/product-brief.md:26:6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet generation and editing.\ndocs/product-brief.md:37:- A user can reopen a session from any stage.\ndocs/product-brief.md:38:- In-progress and completed sessions both appear on the home screen.\ndocs/product-brief.md:49:- The model may propose actions, but a deterministic backend policy layer decides whether each action is valid for the session's current stage.\ndocs/product-brief.md:84:- resume work from prior sessions without losing context\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:83:    sessions: storyteller-sessions\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:103:- `gcs.buckets.sessions`\ndocs/genre-tone-catalog.md:83:That behavior keeps old session references intact while making the active selector options track the\ndocs/README.md:9:- `domain-model.md`: durable session entities, workflow-stage contract, and stage-state rules\ndocs/README.md:14:- `event-taxonomy.md`: append-only event families, payload versioning rules, and helper usage\ndocs/README.md:15:- `realtime-events.md`: session-channel contract, live event families, replay rules, and local auth assumptions\ndocs/README.md:16:- `realtime-events.schema.json`: machine-readable schema bundle for subscription frames and session events\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:10:`frontend/src/features/session/chat/chatToUiActions.ts`.\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:16:- `schema_version`: contract version for the batch payload.\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:36:| `pitches`     | `regenerate_pitches`, `refine_pitch`, `select_pitch`                              | Covers \u201cgive me more options,\u201d \u201crevise that pitch,\u201d and \u201cpick this pitch\u201d flows.                      |\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:47:action, but the later policy engine still has to validate current session state,\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:62:  `select_pitch`, `refine_pitch`, `select_character_sheet`, and\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:82:  \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:85:      \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:97:      \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:113:confirmation gate in the current session state.\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:122:- `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/actions/evaluate` for direct UI or test-driven policy checks\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:123:- `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/chat/intents`, which now includes\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:35:    monkeypatch.setenv(\"STORYTELLER_GCS_SESSIONS_BUCKET_NAME\", \"storyteller-sessions\")\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:50:    assert settings.gcs_bucket_names.sessions == \"storyteller-sessions\"\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:71:            sessions: storyteller-sessions\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:114:            sessions: storyteller-sessions\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:163:    assert settings.gcs_bucket_names.sessions == \"storyteller-dev\"\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:179:    monkeypatch.setenv(\"STORYTELLER_GCS_SESSIONS_BUCKET_NAME\", \"storyteller-sessions\")\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:23:        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:36:2. Policy enforcement: chat-to-UI actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:37:3. Durable orchestration: prompts, structured outputs, retries, and model selection need to be coordinated with persistent session data and job records.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:51:The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:61:- `repositories/`: database access for sessions, events, jobs, and assets\ndocs/ar