      description=\"The home screen could not load prior sessions from the backend. Retry once the API is reachable again.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:149:      eyebrow=\"Recent sessions\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:151:      title=\"Could not load past sessions.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:161:      className=\"sessions-panel\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:163:      title=\"Recent sessions\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:166:        <p className=\"empty-state__title\">No sessions yet.</p>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:169:          session.\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:178:  sessions,\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:182:  sessions: RecentSessionSummary[]\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:186:    <section className=\"session-group\" aria-label={title}>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:187:      <div className=\"session-group__header\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:192:        <Badge tone=\"brand\">{sessions.length}</Badge>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:195:      <ul className=\"session-card-list\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:196:        {sessions.map((session) => {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:197:          const statusCopy = getSessionStatusCopy(session.overall_status)\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:198:          const progress = buildProgressCopy(session)\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:201:            <li key={session.id} className=\"session-card\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:202:              <div className=\"session-card__header\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:204:                  <div className=\"session-card__title-row\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:205:                    <h4>{session.display_title}</h4>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:208:                  <p className=\"session-card__timestamp\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:209:                    Updated {formatUpdatedAt(session.updated_at)}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:218:                  aria-label={`${statusCopy.actionLabel} ${session.display_title}`}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:219:                  to={buildSessionWorkspacePath(session.id)}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:225:              <dl className=\"session-card__meta\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:228:                  <dd>{buildSessionStageSummary(session)}</dd>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:232:                  <dd>{session.selected_genre?.label ?? 'Not selected yet'}</dd>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:237:                    {session.selected_tone_profile?.label ?? 'Not selected yet'}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:243:                aria-label={`${session.display_title} workflow progress`}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:244:                className=\"session-card__progress\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:268:      const session = await createSessionMutation.mutateAsync(undefined)\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:269:      navigate(buildSessionWorkspacePath(session.id))\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:275:  const sessions = recentSessionsQuery.data ?? []\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:283:    ? 'Could not start a new session. Please try again.'\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:285:  const { active, completed } = splitSessionsByStatus(sessions)\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:286:  const totalSessions = sessions.length\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:290:      aria-label=\"Past sessions home screen\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:291:      className=\"sessions-home\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:292:      data-testid=\"sessions-home-route\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:296:        className=\"sessions-home__hero\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:300:              Review in-progress stories, finished reads, and the next session\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:310:        eyebrow=\"Past sessions\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:315:        <div className=\"session-summary-grid\" aria-label=\"Session summary\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:316:          <div className=\"session-summary-card\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:318:            <span>Total sessions</span>\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:320:          <div className=\"session-summary-card\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:324:          <div className=\"session-summary-card\">\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:337:                <InlineSpinner label=\"Starting a new session\" />\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:341:              'Start a new session'\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:345:            New sessions open directly into the workspace shell so the user can\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:361:            className=\"sessions-home__feedback\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:379:          className=\"sessions-panel\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:381:          title=\"Recent sessions\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:385:              description=\"Drafts, active workflows, and sessions that need a refreshed output.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:386:              sessions={active}\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:394:              sessions={completed}\ndocs/domain-model.md:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\ndocs/domain-model.md:7:- The `story_session` is the durable unit of work.\ndocs/domain-model.md:16:The session snapshot returned to the UI should eventually include these fields, even if some land in later prompts:\ndocs/domain-model.md:20:| `id` | Stable UUID for the story session. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:23:| `resume_stage` | Earliest stage that still needs work when a session is reopened. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:26:| `selected_genre_id` | Accepted genre catalog row for the session. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:27:| `selected_tone_profile_id` | Accepted tone profile row for the session. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:28:| `selected_pitch_id` | Accepted pitch record. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:38:`resume_stage` is the key anti-guessing field. The backend computes it from durable stage states so the frontend does not need to infer where to reopen a session by looking at which panels happen to have data.\ndocs/domain-model.md:41:such as pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, and setup revisions point back to the owning\ndocs/domain-model.md:42:session, and the accepted row is tracked on the child record itself. The API snapshot can still\ndocs/domain-model.md:49:| `story_session` | Root aggregate for one bedtime-story project. | IDs, title, stage pointers, overall status, timestamps. | Owns the current accepted choices and job pointers. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:50:| `workflow_stage_state` | Per-stage state for the session. | `session_id`, `stage`, `status`, `updated_at`, `last_event_id`. | Stored explicitly so resume does not depend on sparse child tables. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:53:| `story_brief` | User-authored idea plus any normalized planning summary. | raw brief text, normalized summary, revision number. | Keeps user input separate from later generated planning outputs. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:54:| `pitch` | One candidate story premise. | batch or generation group, summary, hook, bedtime notes, selection flag. | `selected_pitch_id` on the session represents the accepted pitch; selection does not require a separate table. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:55:| `character_sheet` | Accepted cast and character traits for the chosen direction. | protagonist/supporting cast data, revision, generation metadata. | Multiple revisions may exist; the session points at the accepted one. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:56:| `beat_sheet` | Structured Save-the-Cat plan. | ordered beats, bedtime-adaptation notes, revision. | Must be editable and versioned. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:70:| 1 | `genre` | Genre | The user accepts a genre for the session. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:72:| 3 | `brief` | Story brief | The session has an accepted free-form brief and any required normalized summary. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:73:| 4 | `pitches` | Pitches | One pitch is accepted or the user intentionally keeps a current pitch set for further refinement. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:74:| 5 | `characters` | Characters | One character sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:75:| 6 | `beats` | Beat sheet | One beat sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:84:- `frontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts`\ndocs/domain-model.md:96:| `completed` | The stage has an accepted output that is still valid relative to all upstream dependencies. | A beat sheet was accepted and no upstream planning change has made it stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:101:The session-level `overall_status` should be derived, not manually entered:\ndocs/domain-model.md:104:- `in_progress`: at least one stage is `in_progress`, or some stages are completed but the session has not reached a valid finalization state.\ndocs/domain-model.md:106:- `needs_regeneration`: one or more stages are `needs_regeneration`, even if the session also has readable prior outputs.\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:162:1. Planning session reopened midstream:\ndocs/domain-model.md:163:   - Example: `genre`, `tone`, and `brief` are `completed`; `pitches` is `in_progress`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:164:   - Result: open the session on `resume_stage = pitches`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:177:- Frontend mirror for rendering and client-side navigation: `frontend/src/features/session/workflowStages.ts`\ndocs/domain-mod