-running work\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:33:PostgreSQL owns the structured state required to resume a story session.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:37:- session\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:41:- brief, pitch batch, selected pitch\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:42:- character sheet candidates and selection\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:43:- beat sheet\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:66:- WebSockets handle session progress, job status, and incremental event delivery.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:67:- On reconnect, the client should rehydrate from durable session state and recent event history before continuing with live updates.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:69:The websocket channel is a delivery mechanism, not the source of truth. If a socket drops, the session must still be recoverable from PostgreSQL and storage.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:85:- They guide pitch generation, beat planning, and composition prompts.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:110:- Treat the durable event history as product data that can be queried during session resume.\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:23:        session_id=\"session-123\",\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:30:            current_stage_description=\"Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\",\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:34:        session_summary=(\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:48:    assert '\"action_type\": \"refine_pitch\"' in prompt\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:81:                                            \"schema_version\": 1,\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:85:                                                \"I can make the beat sheet moodier \"\nbackend/tests/test_intent_parser_adapter.py:90:                                                \"schema_version\": 1,\nbackend/tests/test