e updates.\n\nIn progress\nReturn home\nLive feed idle\nIn progress\n\nThe workspace is running from the durable snapshot only. Configure the websocket endpoint to start session-scoped live updates.\n\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed idle\n\nReady for notes, approvals, and stage edits from the conversation lane.\n\nSystem\nApr 2, 11:49 AM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Characters.\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 11:49 AM\n\nSelected genre: Quest Fantasy\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 11:49 AM\n\nSelected tone: Hushed Wonder\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 11:49 AM\n\nSelected pitch: Lantern Harbor Promise\n\nAction echo\nApr 2, 11:49 AM\n\nSelected pitch: Otter Bell Moonpath\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nReady\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nRegenerate pitches\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nPress Enter to send. Press Shift+Enter for a new line. Try /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nQueued\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nShape the character sheet\n\nThe character stage will turn the accepted pitch into a durable cast sheet that later planning and writing can trust.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\n\nThe route and the durable session stage are aligned. Live editors and job views can mount here later without changing the URL pattern.\n\nCurrent selection\n\nCharacter sheet pending\n\nNo character sheet is accepted yet. Generate a batch and choose the cast that best supports the selected pitch.\n\nLatest batch\n\nNo character batch yet\n\nThe newest durable batch will appear here once character generation runs.\n\nNext step\n\nChoose one cast to continue\n\nSelecting a character sheet completes this stage and unlocks beat planning.\n\nRevisit pitches\nStart with multiple cast options\nGenerate several cast directions from the accepted pitch so the user can compare different protagonist flaws, support dynamics, and bedtime-safety strategies.\nGenerate a character batch\n\nCreate several cast directions from the accepted pitch, then compare them as durable cards before beats are generated.\n\nGeneration required\nCharacter sheet count\n3 candidates\n4 candidates\n5 candidates\nOptional character guidance\n\nOptional guidance can steer the next cast batch. For example: make the lead more cautious, add a sibling dynamic, or keep the support cast smaller.\n\nGenerate character sheets\nRevisit pitches\nRefine a saved character sheet\n\nPick one saved cast, describe the change, and save the refined result as a new durable option without losing earlier sheets.\n\nSelect a base sheet\nCharacter sheet to refine\nRefinement instructions\n\nDescribe the specific cast change to apply. For example: give the lead a quieter flaw, make the support cast siblings, or add a more obvious comfort ritual.\n\nFocus characters\n\nOptional. Focus the change on specific characters. Separate names with commas or line breaks.\n\nChange summary\n\nOptional. Save a concise durable summary that will show up later in chat and in the saved character history.\n\nPlanning impact\nMajor change\nMinor polish\nRefine character sheet\nNo character sheets have been generated yet\n\nThe character stage keeps every generated batch so the user can resume comparison later instead of losing cast options after each refresh.\n\nGenerate the first batch\n\nPLAN HISTORY\n\nCurrent saved plan\n\nSelected pitch: Otter Bell Moonpath.\n\nRevision 2\nReady for composition\n\nThe next composition pass will bind to the current saved plan 