n,\n  title,\n  ...props\n}: EmptyStateBlockProps) {\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '320,390p' frontend/src/shared/ui/workflow.tsx\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_283", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 557, "prompt_index": 57, "prompt_name": "56 \u2014 Revision History and Branch-Like Tracking for Plan Changes", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T04:51:03-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '520,640p' frontend/src/features/session/PitchSelectionStage.tsx\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "            {isRefining ? 'Refining pitch...' : 'Refine pitch'}\n          </Button>\n          {refinementBasePitch != null ? (\n            <Badge tone=\"neutral\">{refinementBasePitch.title}</Badge>\n          ) : null}\n        </div>\n      </section>\n\n      {latestBatch == null ? (\n        <EmptyStateBlock\n          action={\n            <Button\n              disabled={selectedStage.availability === 'locked' || isGenerating}\n              onClick={() => {\n                void handleGeneratePitches()\n              }}\n              tone=\"primary\"\n            >\n              Generate the first batch\n            </Button>\n          }\n          description=\"The pitch stage will keep every generated batch so the user can come back later and compare old directions against new ones.\"\n          title=\"No pitch cards have been generated yet\"\n        />\n      ) : null}\n\n      {latestBatch != null ? (\n        <section className=\"workspace-stage-panel\">\n          <div className=\"panel-heading\">\n            <div>\n              <h3>Latest pitch batch</h3>\n              <p>\n                The newest batch stays first so the cards are fast to compare.\n                Earlier batches remain below for resume and review.\n              </p>\n            </div>\n            <Badge tone=\"brand\">\n              {formatBatchTimestamp(latestBatch.created_at)}\n            </Badge>\n          </div>\n\n          <CardGrid className=\"pitch-stage__grid\" columns={2}>\n            {latestBatchPitches.map((pitch) => {\n              const selected = pitch.id === selectedPitchId\n              const isPending = pendingPitchId === pitch.id\n\n              return (\n                <SelectionCard\n                  key={pitch.id}\n                  className=\"pitch-stage__card\"\n                  description={readPitchHook(pitch)}\n                  eyebrow={`Pitch ${String(pitch.pitch_index).padStart(2, '0')}`}\n                  footer={\n                    <div className=\"cta-row\">\n                      <Button\n                        disabled={selected || isPending}\n                        onClick={() => {\n                          void handlePitchSelection(pitch)\n                        }}\n                        tone={selected ? 'ghost' : 'primary'}\n                      >\n                        {selected\n                          ? 'Selected pitch'\n                          : isPending\n                            ? 'Saving pitch...'\n                            : 'Choose pitch'}\n                      </Button>\n                    </div>\n                  }\n                  meta={\n                    <div className=\"workspace-stage-detail__badges\">\n                      <Badge tone=\"neutral\">{pitch.generation_key}</Badge>\n                      {pitch.refinement_instructions != null ? (\n                        <Badge tone=\"accent\">Refined</Badge>\n                      ) : null}\n                      {selected ? <Badge tone=\"success\">Selected</Badge> : null}\n                    </div>\n                  }\n                  selected={selected}\n                  title={pitch.title}\n                >\n                  <div className=\"pitch-stage__card-copy\">\n                    <p>\n                      <strong>Central conflict.</strong>{' '}\n                      {readPitchConflict(pitch)}\n                    </p>\n                    <p>\n                      <strong>Why it fits.</strong> {readPitchFitNote(pitch)}\n                    </p>\n                  </div>\n                </SelectionCard>\n              )\n            })}\n          </CardGrid>\n        </section>\n      ) : null}\n\n      {pitchBatches.length > 1 ? (\n        <section className=\"workspace-stage-panel\">\n          <div className=\"panel-heading\">\n            <div>\n              <h3>Earlier pitch batches</h3>\n              <p>\n                Older generations stay available so the user can revisit prior\n                directions instead of losing them after each refresh.\n              </p>\n            </div>\n            <Badge tone=\"neutral\">\n              {pitchBatches.length - 1} earlier batch\n              {pitchBatches.length === 2 ? '' : 'es'}\n            </Badge>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"pitch-stage__history\">\n            {pitchBatches.slice(1).map((batch) => (\n              <SummaryPanel\n                key={batch.generation_key}\n                description={buildBatchSummary(batch)}\n                label=\"Earlier batch\"\n                title={\n                  batch.generation_kind === 'refinement'\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '520,640p' frontend/src/features/session/PitchSelectionStage.tsx\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_284", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 558, "prompt_index": 57, "prompt_name": "56 \u2014 Revision History and Branch-Like Tracking for Plan Changes", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T04:51:03-07:00"}
{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "The built-in JSON spec runner is fine for broad smoke checks, but it can\u2019t assert text inside a specific selector. I\u2019m using a small one-off Puppeteer script for this flow so I can verify the actual current-plan artifact label changes af...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_285", "text": "The built-in JSON spec runner is fine for broad smoke checks, but it can\u2019t assert text inside a specific selector. I\u2019m using a small one-off Puppeteer script for this flow so I can verify the actual current-plan artifact label changes after clicking Restore, not just that the page contains similar words somewhere.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 559, "prompt_index": 57, "prompt_name": "56 \u2014 Revision History and Branch-Like Tracking for Plan Changes", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T04:51:34-07:00"}
